members.name: Grant Deng
members.description: A student currently enrolled in the IB DP program at Johnston Heights secondary, Grant hopes to enjoy life to its fullest. However, this tends to become his way of shirking responsibility. He thinks that he has a sense of humor and always laughs at his own jokes, which, unfortunately are not funny to anybody else. He has engaged in a plethora of random extra-curriculars, and does not remember how he got into any of them. Nonetheless, MUN is something that he is extremely passionate about, particularly the lively, amusing and often quizzical debates.

members.name: Katie Li
members.description: Katie is a Grade 12 IB student at Johnston Heights Secondary and is delighted to be serving as the Director of the Social, Humanitarian, and Cultural Committee (SOCHUM). Upon attending her first conference, she has been drawn by the compelling debates and the fast-paced, energetic environment. Outside of MUN, Katie can be found grinding her coursework, struggling with jazz improvisations on the piano, or undertaking a service project in the community. Katie hopes that JHMUN 2023 will cultivate lasting memories and is ecstatic to be a part of the journey.

members.description: Noah Cho, a second-year IB DP student from Johnston Heights Secondary School, is excited to be participating in JHMUN.
